task.summary: Default task
quick experiment towards launching instances programatically
have script wait for instance to come up and fetch IP address
some more progress. at this point i don't seem to be getting back the standard out but the exit codes make sense for whatever kind of query I am running.

close to 2.2; we've done a version bump for centipede and other dependencies, also added CreateMachineImage, LaunchInstance, and SSH commands. a hardcoded instance id is a problem for CreateMachineImage (not harmful so far as I know). LaunchInstance has hard coded configurations (push out to spring for productionization). Ssh takes an instance id but it defaults to ubuntu as a username, that can be fixed by adding a GetOpt.
This all looks easy to fix but I'm going to drop a version now so I can test the effects of the version bump on the whole pipeline.
switch to onejar packaging so, hopefully, spring can always find the XSD files it wants.
emergency rollback of sdk to 1.6.6 to fix incompatibility with onejar
fix spelling error in comment
version bump so we can separate cleanly from centipede in terms of guava version dependencies because Hadoop holds us back to 11.0.2.

work towards changing sort and grouping orders for PSE3; new comparison operators for triples that are Writable oriented (thus eventually implementable by binary comparison)
tweaks to please JDK8 compiler even though we should be sticking with language level 1.7
develop subject triple comparator and tests, develop PartitionOnSubject and tests, wire up PSE3 to use this. We're just about to bring this up in the remote cluster.
slip in some overrides so I know what is going on in the IDE
remove annotations that broke the build out of the IDE

add some logging so we know what comparators and partitioners were specified. Fixed what looks like a logic bug that could have caused sort comparator to not be assigned if partitioner was not being set.

set the partioner and comparators directly because, it turns out, PSE3 overrides run() and doesn't use the "self aware" stuff
